Write a Python script to summarize the contents of a CSV file. The CSV file will always have three columns.
Column 0: Machine Name
Column 1: Assignee
Column 2: Machine Type

Any entry in column 1 other than whitespace or an empty string must be counted as assigned.
An entry in column 1 of "hwbroken" is a non-functional machine. Count these separately, as they are not assigned to a workload.

The summarization must be written to a markdown file named "summarized.md". The following things must be in the summarization.

1. A table of machine types and other information. For each machine type...
1.a. Show the machine type. The column name is "Machine Type".
1.b. Show the number of machines. The column name is "Machine Count".
1.c. Show the number of unassigned machines. The column name is "Free".
1.d. Show the number of assigned machines. The column name is "Assigned".
1.e. Show the number of non-functional machines. The column name is "BROKEN". 

The Python script should accept exactly one argument, the CSV filename.

